rComments: This class was more challenging than expected & Prof Villeneuve makes you work for your marks, but she's very engaging in lectures, her lessons are organized well & delivered effectively, & it's obvious that she cares about her students. Love that she runs tutorials herself to ensure there's no disconnect between lecture & tutorial. Great prof.

Unlike the rest of the French department: -The course she designed was extremely informative, useful, and fair -She only tests you on what she teaches  She is approachable and helpful and gives useful feedback. She is an objective marker. She uses her insight as a linguist as a teaching tool. Not an easy course but an A is attainable. Worth it.

Extremely harsh marker, with no clear directions for assignments and projects. While she was available for office hours it would have been much more helpful to clarify the concepts in class instead of having 15 people sending emails with the same questions. Poorly structured course. Would recommend avoiding her classes if you can.

She was unclear in describing the assignment requirements and graded the entire class extremely harshly, repeatedly saying, "This is a fourth-year course." Often more than twenty of the thirty students in the class would line up to attend her office hours, to understand why their marks were so harsh when they had followed the instructions exactlly.

She is amazing!! Extremely helpful and positive professor. One of the BEST in school. Her work is pretty hard but she helps everyone as much as she can. Very hard working. Highly recommend to take a course taught by her.
